# Retro App — Project Overview

Real-time retrospective board. No auth. Users generate a room, share a link, and run a structured retro session.

## Architecture

- **Frontend**: Next.js 14+ (App Router) with TypeScript — `/frontend`
- **Backend**: Java 21 + Spring Boot 3 — `/backend`
- **Database**: PostgreSQL 16 with TLS — Spring Data JPA / Hibernate
- **Real-time**: WebSocket (STOMP over SockJS on Spring, SockJS client on Next.js)
- **Monorepo**: `frontend/` and `backend/` directories at repo root

## Database Schema (PostgreSQL 16)

| Table            | PK (UUID) | Key Columns                                                   |
|------------------|-----------|---------------------------------------------------------------|
| `rooms`          | `id`      | `room_code` (UK), `state`, `timer_seconds`, `timer_started_at`, `created_at` |
| `participants`   | `id`      | `room_id` (FK), `username`, `color`, `role`, `session_token`, `joined_at` |
| `board_columns`  | `id`      | `room_id` (FK), `title`, `color`, `position`, `created_at`   |
| `notes`          | `id`      | `room_id` (FK), `column_id` (FK), `participant_id` (FK), `group_id` (FK nullable), `content`, `position` |
| `note_groups`    | `id`      | `room_id` (FK), `column_id` (FK), `name`, `position`         |
| `action_items`   | `id`      | `room_id` (FK), `content`, `position`                        |

All PKs are `UUID`. All entities track `created_at`; `notes` also has `updated_at`.

## Board States (linear, forward-only)

`SETUP → START → REVIEW → DONE`

- **SETUP**: Admin configures columns + timer; lobby shows connected users.
- **START**: Countdown runs. Everyone writes notes. Guests see only their own; admin sees all.
- **REVIEW**: All notes revealed. Admin groups notes via drag-and-drop.
- **DONE**: Summary view. Admin adds action items and can export PDF.

## Key Conventions

- Room IDs are short uppercase alphanumeric codes (e.g. `XK9-47B`).
- First user in a room becomes admin automatically — no login system.
- Guests must pick a username and color before entering the board.
- All mutations flow through WebSocket messages; REST is used only for room creation and PDF export.
- Theme colors: light base `#FBF0D9`, dark base `#0e0e10`. Persisted in `localStorage`.
